While some suspects were simply given fines, others have appeared in various courts across the province.
SAPS spokesperson in the province, Brig Leonard Hlathi, said that the arrests were largely due to normal policing combined with special operations performed by police. ALSO READ: Education MEC shares future plans MEC for Community Safety, Security and Liaison, Vusi Shongwe, applauded the Mpumalanga police. He said that the Department will continue to mobilize communities to help in the fight against crime. Police thanked community members and safety organisations for their roles in bringing these suspects to book. They also urged citizens to work with police to ensure that this momentum is kept.  